# Project Details

## Project Title

**Wanderly – Professional Travel & Holiday Booking Platform**

## Project Description

Wanderly is a responsive travel and holiday booking platform that enables users to explore destinations, discover tour packages, find hotels, and access transportation and travel-related services through a modern and interactive web interface. The platform is designed to simplify travel planning while providing an engaging and user-friendly experience across multiple devices.

## Project Objectives

* Develop a responsive and visually appealing travel booking website.
* Provide users with comprehensive travel information in one platform.
* Enhance user experience through interactive and dynamic web features.
* Demonstrate modern frontend web development techniques and best practices.

## Key Features

* Responsive and mobile-friendly design
* Light and Dark mode support
* User Login and Registration interface
* Destination exploration
* Tour package listings and filtering
* Hotel booking section
* Transportation services
* Food and dining recommendations
* Adventure activity listings
* Travel gallery
* Interactive travel map
* Customer reviews and testimonials
* FAQ section
* Contact form
* Newsletter subscription
* Animated statistics and countdown timer
* Back-to-top navigation

## Technologies Used

* **Frontend:** HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6)
* **Design:** Responsive Web Design, CSS Flexbox, CSS Grid
* **Storage:** Local Storage, Session Storage
* **Tools:** Visual Studio Code, Git, GitHub

## Modules

1. Home Page
2. User Authentication
3. Travel Search & Booking
4. Destination Management
5. Tour Packages
6. Hotel Listings
7. Transport Services
8. Food & Dining
9. Adventure Activities
10. Travel Gallery
11. Customer Reviews
12. FAQ & Contact
13. Newsletter Subscription

## Expected Outcome

The project provides a professional and interactive travel booking platform that offers users a smooth browsing experience, responsive design, and easy access to travel-related services. It showcases frontend development skills, modern UI/UX design principles, and dynamic JavaScript functionality.

